.\AGENTS.md:303:**Quote any mixed-case column identifier** (`"rfqItem_col"`), not just the table name. Sequelize quotes all identifiers, so an unquoted mixed-case column is folded to lowercase by Postgres, producing an orphan column Sequelize can never query (this caused SYS-002 — see §14). Existing migrations already do this (e.g. `"rfqItem_duty_rate_equation"`, `"rfqItem_price_sales_snapshots"`). All-lowercase names (e.g. `factory_country`, `profile_photo`) don't need quoting, but quoting them anyway is harmless and consistent.
