.\AGENTS.md:378:**Actually:** `quote_id` (`RFQVendor_id`) is a sequential integer, so a malicious vendor could enumerate other factories' quotes and POST `updateVendor` / `keepPrice` against them (IDOR). The guard blocks the one real case — a `vendor` whose token `factory_id` differs from the quote's `vendor_id_fk` — and deliberately **fails open** for internal roles, vendors with no `factory_id` on their token (legacy records), and quote rows with no `vendor_id_fk`. The intent is to close the enumeration hole without ever locking out a legitimate user (notably the invite-an-individual-vendor-to-one-item flow, where the invited factory owns its own quote row).
.\AGENTS.md:431:### 2026-05-29 — SYS-002: RFQ grid empty after unquoted `price_sales_snapshots` migration
.\AGENTS.md:433:**What happened:** The RFQ grid showed "no rows to show" with a "Something went wrong (SYS-002)" toast. Every RFQ load failed.
.\AGENTS.md:435:**Root cause:** The `rfqItem_price_sales_snapshots` migration in `models/db.js` was written with an **unquoted** identifier (`ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS rfqItem_price_sales_snapshots`). Postgres folds unquoted identifiers to lowercase, so it created `rfqitem_price_sales_snapshots`. Sequelize quotes all identifiers, so `RFQItem.findAll` queried the case-sensitive `"rfqItem_price_sales_snapshots"` that never existed → `findAll` threw → `Customer.getAll` propagated the error to `controllers/main.controller.js` `findAll`, which returned `sendError(res, err, 'SYS-002')` → empty grid. Every other migration in the file already quoted its identifier; this was the lone exception. The shipped unit test had asserted the *unquoted* form, so CI green-lit the bug.
.\AGENTS.md:437:**Recovery:** Quoted the identifier (commit `a556d3f` → `ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "rfqItem_price_sales_snapshots" TEXT`) and added `ALTER TABLE "RFQItem" DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS "rfqitem_price_sales_snapshots"` (commit `476e453`) to remove the empty lowercase orphan column. Corrected `tests/unit/db.migration.test.js` to require the quoted form and added guards: fail on the unquoted form, assert the orphan DROP exists, assert the correct mixed-case column is never dropped.
.\AGENTS.md:491:**What happened:** RFQ grid column headers (and much more) rendered as garbage — `备注` showed as boxes/junk, `中国` as `Σ╕¡σ¢╜`, `Décor` as `D├⌐cor`, `Cortázar` as `Cort├ízar`, `©` as `┬⌐`, `'` as `ΓÇÖ`. The 12 visible RFQ header rows were the tip; a tripwire scan (looking for the box-drawing/garbage bytes that never occur in real data) flagged corruption in **thousands of additional rows across ~20+ text columns** — vendor/factory country, item descriptions, user last names, merch group, licensing feedback, vendor notes/addresses, audit-log history, email templates.
