src/app/pages/rfq\README.md:90:### Fill handle: keep drag-copy, block double-click fill-down
src/app/pages/rfq\README.md:93:The master RFQ grid still enables AG Grid fill-handle drag-copy through `cellSelection.handle: { mode: 'fill', direction: 'y', setFillValue }`. `rfq.component.ts` also installs `installFillHandleDoubleClickBlocker()` on grid ready, which catches `dblclick` events on `.ag-fill-handle` during the capture phase and stops AG Grid from auto-filling down the grid.
src/app/pages/rfq\README.md:96:Double-clicking the selected-cell fill handle copied a Tech Pack Link value down the displayed grid and destroyed many row values. Users still need normal drag-to-copy, so removing the fill handle is not acceptable.
src/app/pages/rfq\README.md:99:Do not "fix" this by setting `suppressFillHandle: true` globally or removing `cellSelection.handle`; that breaks drag-copy. AG Grid v35.1 docs expose the fill handle as an on/off feature and do not document a narrower double-click-only setting, so keep the event blocker unless AG Grid adds a first-class option. Verify with `rfq.component.spec.ts` tests for drag fill and double-click blocking.
src/app/pages/rfq\README.md:118:AG Grid records edits, fill-handle operations, paste, delete, undo, and redo through `cellValueChanged`; the custom snapshot restore did not reliably cover fill/copy/paste and could restore stale server data.
